channel.title: RuneScape Packets
channel.description: If I wanted to find out information about a specific packet (i.e. what it does), where would I start?

item.title: RuneScape Packets
item.dc:creator: @zstars zstars
item.description:
@zstars wrote:

Zachera:

If I wanted to find out information about a specific packet (i.e. what it does), where would I start?

Assuming we are talking about the real Runescape and not a private server, you could start by getting a deob and a debugger. Then you can locate and set a breakpoint on the packet stream class or the opcode encryption / decryption methods, and move from there

This technique has been proven to work somewhat efficiently, if you need more info feel free to contact me (preferibly on irc), I’m always interested in RS packet hacking.

Read full topic

item.description:
@qauters wrote:

vbcoderx:

find the method that is usually refered to as parsepacket… qauters has it named server message listener… it would be most helpful, if you refactor a client, so when you look at the parsepacket method, it makes it easier to understand what it does… or you could just log all the traffic :-p

I haven’t named it that, it’s named that because it modifies the method, to log server messages (like “You have mined an iron ore!”) to the bot.
